    {
      "id": "CVE-2026-49941",
      "publishedDate": "2026-06-04T16:07:20.739Z",
      "lastModifiedDate": "2026-06-04T16:07:20.739Z",
      "description": "Net::CIDR::Set versions through 0.20 for Perl did not validate IP addresses.\n\nThe add method called the _encode method to parse addresses. If the addresses did not look like netmasks or network ranges, then they were assumed to single IP addresses and passed back to itself as a 32-bit or 128-bit netmask.\n\nIf the argument was not a well-formed IP address, then this would lead to indefinite recursion.\n\nAn attacker could use this to cause a denial of service.",
      "severity": "N/A",
      "references": [
        {
          "url": "https://metacpan.org/release/RRWO/Net-CIDR-Set-0.21/changes",
          "type": "reference"
